column5: Congrats to all.  Looks like everyone is doing great.  Can't ask for any more than that.
Congratulations brother! Jim

Congratulations to you and your wife on the birth of a healthy baby girl  Enjoy every minute as they grow up fast, and yes get ready to hear all those "I kicked you butt fishing today Dad" or the famous "What's that smell? Smells like a skunk in here"   Yes BTW these sayings I know from experience
Congrats!
Wha a nice additition to the family:) Congrulations!!
Congrads! Just think, in 13 years you won't know anything  , up until then you will have all the answers. Been 19 years for me now, and love every second of it!
That's awesome brother!!!    WOW an 8 pounder to boot, your wife's a trooper! lol Congrats on your new fishin' partner, and best wishes from myself and the family.  Cheers, Ryan

hi we are expecting a new addition too , we go in monday for induction (will post pics too). Congrats to your new family and i hope all goes well for you. Good luck and tight lines to you  bigredfisher

I have been waiting for this for a long time now. Could not be prouder parents. My little baby girl  Rylea was born today at 7:28am. Baby is healthy and Mom is doing awesome. I'm on top of the world today for sure.  I cant wait till she can hold that little pink fishing rod. Rylea  Me and Rylea (Those little eyes make me melt everytime)  My wife and I and our little baby girl    All my friends told me what would happen and the feelings but nothing can prepare you for the sensational feeling you get when you first get to hold your first little one.
real cutie, congrats to u n ur wife
congrats to you and your wife
thats awesome bro, congrats! another thing to prepare for... the day she outfishes u with that little pink rod! lol... oh, and boys one day too. lol. congrats man, enjoy every minute with her!

congrats to  all 3 of you!  momma looks to be healthy afterwards, u seem to be pumped and a gorgeous little girl, best of luck in the next few months with all 3 of your's health!  your gonna regret teachin her to fish, dont come crying to us when she's kickin your tail on the water!  Matt!

Congrats. I've got two  girls of my own ( and also a little guy). Funny, my oldest now 20 years old, still comes out will us to drop a line in when ever she can. I started them young and have enjoyed every minute I spend with them fishing. Enjoy her now, they grow up real fast.  All the best!!
Congrats to the new family!!!
Congratulations. You have just embarked on a life long adventure. Enjoy the ride with it's highs and lows.
Great stuff!  I've been a father for 7 weeks, oh the stories I can tell... and many that I won't.
Good stuff. I was in yer shoes 34 years ago for the first time. The doctor suggested that I sit down. Said I looked like I wuz gonna pass out.  JF
Congrats Smallie, great looking family.  Her eyes are wide open already, probably already eyeing all your fishing gear  Jose
Congtat's to all of you.

Congratulations on the new addition to your family and things will never be the same for you again, and that's a good thing   There's nothing in this world as precious as your children.  It's been nearly 42 years since I  became a father for the 1st time, yet the memories of that night are as fresh in my mind as if it happened yesterday.  You've just taken the 1st step in a wonderful experience !!
Congrats to you and the family! No OFC logo on the cap? LOL
Congrats   ...

Congratulations on the new addition. Your lives have just changed forever, for the better. Enjoy and cherish each and every day as they grow way too quickly. It was 33 years ago for me and it seems like last week!
Congrats... its a great feeling....
Love the second photo ' who the heck are you!' LOL  Congrats  TB
Nice Keeper! Congrates
Congrats man, you'll never forget this day.  Take good care of those ladies!  Sinker
Awesome brother. Real nice addition to the family.  Congrats to all.
Congratulations!  A beautiful addition.
congratulations! lovely child
CONGRATULATIONS....i dont want my wife to see this post, she's due any day now and sick of being pregnant!   What a beautiful baby, the second picture is really great.
